*FALL 2024 SCHEDULE — UPDATED LOCATIONS INCLUDED* (old text below)

Привет всем! RUSS IS BACK for another amazing year! 🤩

We hope you’ve all had a restful and fun summer! Here is our ✨OFFICIAL EXTRA CREDIT SCHEDULE✨ for the Fall 2024 semester!! Whether it’s Help Desk, Translation Club, Conversation Club, or Movie Night, we’ve got you covered!!

👉And check back here for info on upcoming EVENTS (new and old) … psst we’ll be posting about one very soon!

❗️Some weekdays have changed since last year, so make sure to take note of them!
An introspective experience for sure… It’s not just me, right?🫣

Another year, another LLC Collab😎

Join us next Thursday, November 14, for games, drinks, and an opportunity to practice Spanish, German, and Russian in our annual @clashsa.mcgill x @russmcgill x @gsamcgill LLC Social! Free admission provided with one food or drink purchase.

📍 Ye Olde Orchard, 20 Prince Arthur St W
⏰ 7PM

Find out if Carleton University’s EURUS MA Program is right for you!🎓

One of the program directors, Jeff Sahadeo, will be providing a pizza lunch and information about EURUS!

Please RSVP to Dr. Daniel Pratt if you will be attending the in-person session: daniel.pratt@mcgill.ca

N PERSON SESSION:
Date: Thursday, November 7th, 2024
Time: 1:30 pm
Location: Slavic Library (Sherbrooke 680, rm 309)

VIRTUAL SESSION:
Date: Thursday, November 21st, 2024
Time: 6-7 pm
Where: ONLINE (https://carleton-ca.zoom.us/j/98609662405)

EVENT ANNOUNCEMENT📣

Attend an event TOMORROW with famous public poet, writer, journalist, film critic, and screenwriter, Dmitry Bykov! 

When: Tomorrow, November 2 @7 pm
Where: Salle Marie-Stéphane, École de musique Vincent-d’Indy, 628 Chemin de la Côte-Sainte-Catherine, Outremont

McGill Students get 30% off their ticket with the promo code McGill30 (student ID required at entry)

GET YOUR TICKETS HERE: https://karabas.ca/events/bykov-2024/
